 Lawton, Werner Menski, Eleanor Nesbitt, Alan Brown and Azim Nanji.Additions for this new edition include subsections on reproduction, vegetarianism, just war and terrorism, and genetic modification. The book is structured so that topics can be explored within a specific tradition or comparatively across the traditions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aEthics. 0aReligion and ethics. 0aReligions. 0aReligious ethicsvComparative studies. 0aReligious ethics. 4aPhilosophy. 7aRELIGION / Ethics.2bisacsh1 aBrown, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawton, Clive A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLawton, Clive, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aMenski, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorgan, Peggy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNanji, Azim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNesbitt, Eleanor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311078046840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978074863002840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780748630028423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780748630028/original  a978-3-11-078046-8  Edinburgh University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-2000c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK